{{- define "doer-tools" -}}
{{- if eq .Role "coder"}}

CODER TOOLS:
- liza_submit_for_review — Submit completed work for review
  {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "commit_sha": "<SHA>", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"}
  Get SHA first: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD
- liza_handoff — Context near exhaustion (~90%)
  {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "summary": "<what is done>", "next_action": "<exact next step>", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"}
  Optional structured fields: "succeeded" (array), "failed" (array), "hypothesis" (string), "key_files" (array), "dead_ends" (array)
  When provided, structured fields override summary/next_action for richer handoff context.
- liza_mark_blocked — Cannot proceed (spec ambiguity, missing dependency)
  {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}", "reason": "<what is blocking>", "questions": ["<q1>", "<q2>"]}
- liza_write_checkpoint — Write pre-execution checkpoint (REQUIRED before submission)
  {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}", "intent": "<what>", "validation_plan": "<how to verify>", "files_to_modify": ["<file1>"]}
  Optional: "assumptions", "risks", "tdd_not_required", "scope_extensions"
  scope_extensions: [{"file": "<path>", "justification": "<why this out-of-scope file must change>"}]
  If you need to modify a file outside the task scope, declare it as a scope_extension — not as an assumption.
{{- else if eq .Role "code-planner"}}

CODE PLANNER TOOLS:
- liza_submit_for_review — Submit code plan for review
  {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "commit_sha": "<SHA>", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"}
  Get SHA first: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD
- liza_write_checkpoint — Write pre-execution checkpoint (REQUIRED before submission)
  {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}", "intent": "<what>", "validation_plan": "<how to verify>", "files_to_modify": ["<file1>"]}
- liza_set_task_output — Persist structured task definitions for downstream task creation
  {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}", "output": [
    {"desc": "...", "done_when": "...", "scope": "...", "spec_ref": "...", "depends_on": ["0", "2"]}
  ]}
  depends_on: optional array of sibling index strings. "0" means "depends on output[0]".
  Indices are resolved to child task IDs at transition time.
- liza_mark_blocked — Cannot proceed
  {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}", "reason": "<what is blocking>", "questions": ["<q1>", "<q2>"]}
{{- else if eq .Role "epic-planner"}}

EPIC PLANNER TOOLS:
- liza_submit_for_review — Submit epic plan for review
